snippet.textDisplay: The best I have been doing is using edjing and buying stuff from iTunes. I’ve had the most fun with The Plague from The Prince of Egypt, as well as songs by Two Steps From Hell. Playing the same song with two discs is fun, especially having them a split second apart, creating an echo. There’s also speeding them up and slowing them down, with the option of it sounding normal or distorted (low tone for slow on distorted, high pitched for fast) they tried to make me pay a subscription to use the app I got and used for free later, I somehow got around it by reentering the app, and rating it with a honest complaint about it, it’s the only good free to use DJ app with purchasable add ons, better stay free, subscription crap is robbery, especially at such ridiculous prices. $8 a week? Get real. Not even doing $8 a month. $0.99 a every two months is preferable, maybe even $1.50 or $1.99 at the most, but that’s too far for something like this that probably won’t be used every week or even every month.
